{
  "stem": "10768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Chortkiv was somewhere on the eastern part of Poland already, I believe in, in, in-- I don't know exactly where Chortkiv was.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But Chortkiv, I think, was near-- further than Stanislawow and Tarnopol, close to the Romanian border.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my grandfather was very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were other little, little shtiebel, I would say, little synagogues.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All of them had at least 400 or 500 people praying at one time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had a very old, prominent synagogue, which was very-- the structure was very old but yet very solid.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was 300, minimum 300 years old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So our town really started, had a history of about 300 or more years of existence-- of Jewish, of Jewish population existence.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Very possible that after the Spanish Inquisition, when there was a movement from Spain into, let's say, Germany and part of them were accepted by the Polish ruler, who was at that time accepting the Jews into Poland.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is when the Jews settled in our town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Do any of these synagogues remain today, as far as you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To my knowledge, the entire Jewish city-- the entire-- not the city, but the entire Jewish part of the city-- was destroyed except for the big synagogue, where some of the chandeliers were probably taken out and other things.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But now it's a museum.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Germans did not destroy, destroy this synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was so built-- the walls were so thick, they would have-- they probably could not destroy it anyhow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there is now a museum.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And even if somebody goes to the city, they go to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If somebody goes back to Poland to our city, they go to see the museum-- whatever's left there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What was your experience?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
